        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The id and name for a Zend_Form_Element_File element will not be rendered using array notation (when they are part of  a subform or the belongsTo property is set). See ZF-5864 for the reasons behind doing so.\r\n\r\nHowever the for attribute of an accompanying label still gets rendered as if array notation would be used, see the rendered html below:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n<div class=\"element\">\r\n<label for=\"pictures-0-file\" class=\"optional\">Picture (max 4MB each)<\/label>\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"MAX_FILE_SIZE\" value=\"4194304\" id=\"MAX_FILE_SIZE\" \/>\r\n<input type=\"file\" name=\"file\" id=\"file\" \/>\r\n<\/div>\r\n<div class=\"element\">\r\n<label for=\"pictures-0-caption\" class=\"optional\">Caption<\/label>\r\n<input type=\"text\" name=\"pictures[0][caption]\" id=\"pictures-0-caption\" value=\"\" size=\"15\" \/>\r\n<\/div>\r\n{code}"
        },
